-- Nordic Electricity Prices Increase as Drier Weather Forecast
-- B y   T o r s t e n   F a g e r h o l m
-- 2013-04-29T09:48:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-29/nordic-electricity-prices-increase-as-drier-weather-forecast.html
Price of electricity for delivery
from July through September gains 1.8% to EU37.60/MWh on Nasdaq
OMX Group’s energy exchange at 1123am in Oslo.
* Hydro and snow levels forecast to be 20.8TWh below seasonal
norm in two weeks, compared with 20.7TWh estimated on April 26,
Markedskraft data on Bloomberg show
* “ Weather forecasts  indicate a drier development at end of the
prediction period, underpinning prices, while other price-
driving factors are little changed”: Anders Engkvist, chief
analyst at power trader Bixia in Linkoeping, Sweden
* NOTE: Nordic area meets more than half of power needs by
running water through turbines
* Nordic May contract rises 1.8% to EU36.80/MWh  To contact the reporter on this story:
